# Trashbot — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a self-improving agent that learns from 80,000 real SWE-agent trajectories.
It extracts rules from failed vs passing attempts and injects them into the agent's prompt.

## Data
- 80,036 trajectories in `data/swe-agent-trajectories/data/*.parquet`
- 10 curated traces in `failed_traces/10_traces_to_fix/` (each has failed + passing attempts)
- Baseline: 16.7% success rate, 83.3% failure rate
- Generated rules in `rules/rules_v1.md`

## Key Commands
- `python scripts/generate_rules.py` — extract rules from traces
- `python scripts/generate_rules.py --append-to CLAUDE.md` — extract and inject into agent prompt
- `python query_traces.py --id <instance_id>` — look up any trace
- `python scripts/phase1_pipeline.py` — load and validate dataset
- `python scripts/phase2_baseline.py` — compute baseline KPIs

## Code Style
- Python 3.10+, type hints where helpful
- Keep it simple — no unnecessary abstractions
- Scripts go in `scripts/`, modules in `src/`
- Rules output goes in `rules/`

## When Working on This Project
- Always activate venv first: `source .venv/bin/activate`
- Check `rules/rules_v1.md` for the latest generated rules
- The self-improving loop: traces → rules → CLAUDE.md → agent uses rules → new traces
- Failed traces have both `failed_traces` and `passing_trace` — always compare both
